com.camerontec.catalys.util.marketdata

Interface IInstrumentDepthListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IInstrumentMarketDataListener
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IMarketDataBuffer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MarketDataBuffer

    public interface IInstrumentDepthListener
extends IInstrumentMarketDataListener
    Objects that want to listen for depth or detail updates should implement this interface.

    Note that the same call back interface is used for both depth and detail (unaggregated) updates.

    • Method Detail

      • onDepthChange

        boolean onDepthChange(IInstrument instrument,
                      boolean aggregated,
                      IDetailEntry[] buyDepth,
                      IDetailEntry[] sellDepth)
        Called when whole depth has changed.
        Parameters:
        instrument - Instrument whose depth has changed.
        aggregated - True if aggregated depth, false if not (ie detail).
        buyDepth - Buy side depth entries
        sellDepth - Sell side depth entries
        Returns:
        true if this listener does not want be notified further - ie it is requesting the source to remove it from the source's list of listeners.

      • onDepthEntryAdd

        boolean onDepthEntryAdd(IInstrument instrument,
                        boolean aggregated,
                        int entryID,
                        boolean buy,
                        int price,
                        int qty,
                        IMarketDataItem[] values)
        Called when a particular depth entry has been added.

        IMPORTANT NOTE

        The values array is reused - so you should not store a reference to it. You should not process the full array. Processing of the array should terminate once an entry with a 0 fieldID is encountered.
        Parameters:
        instrument - Instrument whose depth has changed.
        aggregated - True if aggregated depth, false if not (ie detail).
        entryID - ID of entry being added.
        buy - True if this is a buy side entry.
        price - Price level of this entry.
        qty - Quantity of entry.
        values - Other information associated with entry. May be null.
        Returns:
        true if this listener does not want be notified further - ie it is requesting the source to remove it from the source's list of listeners.

      • onDepthEntryChange

        boolean onDepthEntryChange(IInstrument instrument,
                           boolean aggregated,
                           int entryID,
                           boolean buy,
                           int price,
                           int qty,
                           IUpdateEntry[] changes)
        Called when a particular depth entry has changed or been deleted.

        Deleted depth entries cause this to be called with qty == 0.

        IMPORTANT NOTE

        The changes array is reused - so you should not store a reference to it. You should not process the full array. Processing of the array should terminate once an entry with a 0 fieldID is encountered.
        Parameters:
        instrument - Instrument whose depth has changed.
        aggregated - True if aggregated depth, false if not (ie detail).
        entryID - ID of entry being changed.
        buy - True if this is a buy side entry.
        price - Price level of this entry.
        qty - Quantity of entry.
        changes - Other information associated with entry. May be null.
        Returns:
        true if this listener does not want be notified further - ie it is requesting the source to remove it from the source's list of listeners.
